  "prompt": "Can I send 500 and 1000 rs cash notes to India through USPS mail from USA?",
  "response": "As of 2016, the Indian government demonetized the 500 and 1000 rupee notes, meaning they are no longer considered legal tender. Consequently, sending these notes to India via USPS or any other mailing service would be futile as they have no monetary value.\n\nFurthermore, even if you intend to send currently valid Indian currency notes, international mailing of cash is generally discouraged due to the risk of theft, loss, and various postal and customs regulations. Instead, consider using secure methods such as electronic transfers, bank drafts, or money transfer services that are designed for safely transmitting funds internationally.",
